A collection of a few watercolors I’ve been working on last month- each for sale for $150, unframed but comes matted and ready to fit into a frame, free shipping to the USA ❤️ sizes vary (most fit in an 8”x10” frame but the one of the man will fit in a 5”x7” frame) feel free to comment or DM me here on Instagram to purchase, or email shumakerart@gmail.com if interested or if you have any questions on any of these watercolor paintings 🌻 model with red gloves is the beautiful @monett_corona

WIP🌻 Painting in the details at this stage is so much fun! This is now my 4th layer on the face. I was trying a Caravaggio technique tutorial that I saw on YouTube but I abandoned the technique - I don’t have the patience to wait as long on this one for many more layers to dry but I will try on another piece so I can see how it compares. In my head - more glazes will increase the depth of the work, which is my goal. Now I just have to work on the other arm 🌻

“Alice’s Garden” Oil Paint on Panel in a vintage oval frame 🐇 Will be on display and for sale at @cityarts_orlando Alice in Wonderland Exhibition opening this Third Thursday, April 20th ! Swipe to see the painting on a wall | This piece features many of the flowers in the singing flower scene, including: roses, irises, daisies, pansies, tulips, sweetpeas, blue bonnets, violets, calla lily, lily of the valley, lilac, sunflowers, chrysanthemums, morning glories, daffodils, tiger lily (my personal favorite!), dandelion, white rose, thistle, yellow daisies, and a rose bud 🌹🌷🌻

“Alice’s Garden” Making of 🌻🌹🌷 On Display & For Sale this Thursday April 20th 6-9pm at @cityarts_orlando for the Alice in Wonderland show 🐇 So many amazing pieces, this is one you don’t want to miss ❤️

Just got done with this mural in Sioux City, IA. So happy to work again with @shumakerart we make a great team! 
The mural is titled “Hope is a Thing with Sequins” which is a nod to the Emily Dickinson poem “Hope is the Thing with Feathers” which compares hope to a bird.

Dappled by light 🌞 portrait of my dear friend @a.moonsang 🌙 oil paint on wood panel

Made a new mural for @prairiehousecoffeeco 🦬❤️ in Oakland, FL 🌞 So honored to have been given this opportunity and was approached to do a landscape with Canadian homage- they do the most delicious coffees, food, natural wine and sweet treats in a beautiful cozy space so go check them out if you haven’t already ❤️ The owners are lovely sisters who pour their heart and soul into every creation. This mural features Canadian Geese, Prairies, and my favorite part- a mother and baby Bison 🥲 had 3 days to start and complete which was a fun challenge 🎉 Big thank you to @_ryansemple for helping ❤️🦬

All done painting the mayor Lulu for @stackssquares in ATL, GA! Thought I’d bring a piece of my home to this mural festival🌻🥰🐈‍⬛ Lulu is a kitty that explores around the Thornton Park area in Orlando and is known to frequent the bars and businesses in the area so they declared Lulu mayor 🌟 Thank you to @mattkellerlehman_photo for allowing me to use this wonderful image of Lulu to reference for a mural 😊 

A huge thank you to @yoyocam for having us be a part of this wonderful opportunity 🌻 and a huge thank you to @_ryansemple for helping me paint ❤️ had so much fun and there’s so many beautiful murals that every artist made! Be sure to check it out 🌟 

#muralart #muralpainting #muralartist #mural #shumakerart #luluunleashed #luluformayor #muralartwork #stackssquares

New mural process video “Night Owl” at @burtonsthorntonpark in Orlando, FL ❤️🦉🌕 This mural features one of my favorite feathered friends- the beautiful and wise Barn Owl, a glowing full moon and night blooming Queen of the Night flowers and is located in @thorntonpark | So much fun! Thank you to Lisa and Aaron for making this happen ❤️ The barn owl is my favorite alongside the Harpy Eagle. What is your favorite bird?

Full view of “Night Owl” mural at @burtonsthorntonpark featuring a wise Barn Owl, night blooming Queen of the Night Flowers, and a super moon 🌝 Thanks again Lisa and Aaron for making this happen! Such a fun project 🦉❤️ Having fun with non-human subjects lately, a fun challenge 😊🌻 p.s. I totally grew a few inches taller in the 2nd picture 😅 secret ability 🤫 but truly first picture is accurate to mural size next to a 5’6 lady

Auction now live! 3 new acrylic pieces tonight at @abvgallery for their “PRISMATIC” group show. The exhibition features 130 works by 30 artists. Each artist selected 3 different monochromatic color palettes for each of their three pieces. 🌈
 
It was fun to play with the fluid nature of acrylic that I don’t get to do very often with oil painting. Adding drips and fluorescent pigments to bring up the intensity of the paintings 🌟 model for the yellow painting is the amazing @monett_corona ❤️

These pieces are 12”x12” with painted sides and ready to hang. Click the link in @abvgallery bio for the online auction! Auction ends 11/19 at 6pm EST ❤️🌟

I turned 30 this week and my partner, Nick, surprised me with the most beautiful oil portrait of me by one of my favorite artists, Sabrina Shumaker.  She turned me into the ethereal glitter princess of all strange and lovely creatures that I’ve always aspired to be. The perfect encapsulation of me at 30. There are so many precious little details. I’m wearing an emerald ring that I made. The troll has a diamond earring. I’m on a mound of diamond dust. My hair and makeup is Dolly Parton inspired. I feel seen and I’ll cherish this forever. Thank you!! @nick_turbo_art @shumakerart
